## Summary
- route fire-and-forget `sessions_send` messages directly into active run-scoped targets when possible
- fall back to the durable parent session key if transcript-commit steering is rejected, so pending pingbacks are not stranded on an ended run
- add regression coverage for a `[TASK-COMPLETE]` pingback targeting a blocked cron run session

Fixes #86586

## Real behavior proof
Behavior addressed: A faster callee can send a fire-and-forget `sessions_send` pingback to a caller's run-scoped cron session while the caller run is still blocked by a slower sibling tool call. If the active-run queue rejects before committing that pingback to the transcript, this patch reroutes the pending message to the durable parent session key instead of leaving it orphaned on the ended run.

Real environment tested: Local OpenClaw source runtime on this branch, invoked with Node through the repository TypeScript loader. The reproduction used the production `createSessionsSendTool` path and the embedded-run active session registry, then captured the actual terminal output below.

Exact steps or command run after this patch:
```sh
node --import tsx --input-type=module <<'EOS'
import { createSessionsSendTool } from './src/agents/tools/sessions-send-tool.ts';
import { setActiveEmbeddedRun, testing as embeddedRunsTesting } from './src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/runs.ts';

embeddedRunsTesting.resetActiveEmbeddedRuns();
const runScopedCallerKey = 'agent:leasing-ops:cron:monthly-utility:run:run-fast';
const durableCallerKey = 'agent:leasing-ops:cron:monthly-utility';
const gatewayAgentCalls = [];
const queueEvents = [];
setActiveEmbeddedRun('caller-active-session', {
  queueMessage: async (text, options) => {
    queueEvents.push({ sessionId: 'caller-active-session', text, options });
    throw new Error('active session ended before queued steering message was committed');
  },
  isStreaming: () => true,
  isCompacting: () => false,
  supportsTranscriptCommitWait: true,
  abort: () => {},
}, runScopedCallerKey);
const tool = createSessionsSendTool({
  agentSessionKey: 'agent:re-portal:main',
  agentChannel: 'telegram',
  callGateway: async (request) => {
    if (request.method === 'agent') {
      gatewayAgentCalls.push(request.params);
      return { runId: 'fallback-run', status: 'accepted', acceptedAt: Date.now() };
    }
    return {};
  },
  config: {
    session: { mainKey: 'main', scope: 'per-sender', agentToAgent: { maxPingPongTurns: 0 } },
    tools: { sessions: { visibility: 'all' }, agentToAgent: { enabled: true } },
  },
});
const result = await tool.execute('proof-run-scoped-pingback', {
  sessionKey: runScopedCallerKey,
  message: '[TASK-COMPLETE] re-portal occupancy ready',
  timeoutSeconds: 0,
});
await new Promise((resolve) => setTimeout(resolve, 25));
const details = result.details;
const fallbackCall = gatewayAgentCalls.find((call) => call.sessionKey === durableCallerKey);
const runScopedGatewayCallSeen = gatewayAgentCalls.some((call) => call.sessionKey === runScopedCallerKey);
console.log(JSON.stringify({
  scenario: 'run-scoped sessions_send pingback fallback',
  toolResult: {
    status: details.status,
    sessionKey: details.sessionKey,
    deliveryStatus: details.delivery?.status,
  },
  activeRunQueueAttempt: {
    sessionId: queueEvents[0]?.sessionId,
    containsTaskComplete: queueEvents[0]?.text?.includes('[TASK-COMPLETE] re-portal occupancy ready') === true,
    waitForTranscriptCommit: queueEvents[0]?.options?.waitForTranscriptCommit === true,
    deliveryTimeoutMs: queueEvents[0]?.options?.deliveryTimeoutMs,
  },
  fallbackDelivery: {
    sessionKey: fallbackCall?.sessionKey,
    containsTaskComplete: fallbackCall?.message?.includes('[TASK-COMPLETE] re-portal occupancy ready') === true,
    runScopedGatewayCallSeen,
  },
}, null, 2));
embeddedRunsTesting.resetActiveEmbeddedRuns();
EOS
```

Evidence after fix: Terminal output from the command above:
```json
{
  "scenario": "run-scoped sessions_send pingback fallback",
  "toolResult": {
    "status": "accepted",
    "sessionKey": "agent:leasing-ops:cron:monthly-utility:run:run-fast",
    "deliveryStatus": "pending"
  },
  "activeRunQueueAttempt": {
    "sessionId": "caller-active-session",
    "containsTaskComplete": true,
    "waitForTranscriptCommit": true,
    "deliveryTimeoutMs": 30000
  },
  "fallbackDelivery": {
    "sessionKey": "agent:leasing-ops:cron:monthly-utility",
    "containsTaskComplete": true,
    "runScopedGatewayCallSeen": false
  }
}
```

Observed result after fix: The active run-scoped delivery was attempted with transcript-commit waiting, the pending `[TASK-COMPLETE]` payload was preserved, and the fallback delivery targeted the durable cron session `agent:leasing-ops:cron:monthly-utility` with no gateway agent delivery to the ended run-scoped key.

What was not tested: I did not connect to the reporter's private production host, Telegram account, or local cron log files.

